Listen!

4
00:01:04,781 --> 00:01:07,773
Do you hear it?

5
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:16,724
Go away!

6
00:01:16,827 --> 00:01:19,457
You all have to go away!

7
00:01:29,306 --> 00:01:30,398
No!

8
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:48,853
It's not in my head.

9
00:01:49,459 --> 00:01:51,359
Bobby.

10
00:01:51,461 --> 00:01:54,453
Bobby, where are you?

11
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:59,157
Bobby.

12
00:01:59,269 --> 00:02:02,432
Bobby, why aren't you here?

13
00:02:06,676 --> 00:02:08,911
It's happening again.

14
00:02:08,912 --> 00:02:11,176
Shh, shh...

15
00:02:14,484 --> 00:02:17,476
They're after me.

16
00:02:21,925 --> 00:02:24,093
I'm not crazy.
I'm not crazy.

17
00:02:24,094 --> 00:02:26,819
You hear them, don't you?

18
00:02:36,006 --> 00:02:37,769
No.

19
00:02:37,874 --> 00:02:38,874
No!

20
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:16,779
Well, they're hiring
non-unions...

21
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:21,450
...down at sanitation,
if you're interested.

22
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,885
There's nothing
in transportation?

23
00:03:22,886 --> 00:03:23,986
Not at the moment.

24
00:03:23,987 --> 00:03:27,617
Do you have any other
job skills?

25
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:29,785
Good mechanic.

26
00:03:29,893 --> 00:03:34,029
Got a lot of mechanics waiting
for work already.

27
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:37,466
All right, now what time will I
expect you to call me tonight?

28
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:40,095
About what?

29
00:03:40,203 --> 00:03:41,937
Well, it says here you got
a board release.

30
00:03:41,938 --> 00:03:45,613
Do you understand
what that means?

31
00:03:46,409 --> 00:03:47,776
I've never done this before.

32
00:03:47,777 --> 00:03:50,412
It means parole
on a short leash.

33
00:03:50,413 --> 00:03:51,513
So you call...

34
00:03:51,514 --> 00:03:53,315
...in the next 24 hours
and let me know...

35
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:56,418
...where you're parking
yourself tonight.

36
00:03:56,419 --> 00:03:59,355
I'm staying at my mother's.

37
00:03:59,356 --> 00:04:00,456
All right.

38
00:04:00,457 --> 00:04:04,827
You come in every Tuesday
for the next six months.

39
00:04:04,828 --> 00:04:07,296
Now, this is important,
because you miss one...,

40
00:04:07,297 --> 00:04:10,232
...you're in violation.

41
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,067
Does your mother know
you're staying with her?

42
00:04:12,068 --> 00:04:13,068
No.

43
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:16,772
Well, don't you think
you should call and tell her?

44
00:04:16,773 --> 00:04:19,783
She died while I was inside.

45
00:04:21,611 --> 00:04:22,711
I'm sorry to hear that.

46
00:04:22,712 --> 00:04:25,817
Do you have any other family?

47
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,954
Call him in the morning.

48
00:04:31,955 --> 00:04:33,946
He may have work.

49
00:04:34,057 --> 00:04:35,324
Not a lot of employers...

50
00:04:35,325 --> 00:04:39,715
...want to hire people
in your situation.

51
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:02,852
Need something?

52
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,714
Helen Reynolds' son.

53
00:06:05,715 --> 00:06:06,815
I left you that message.

54
00:06:06,816 --> 00:06:07,916
Oh, yeah, yeah.

55
00:06:07,917 --> 00:06:11,011
Of course, 519.

56
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:14,113
Wait here.

57
00:06:25,568 --> 00:06:27,703
I don't know where I'm going.

58
00:06:27,704 --> 00:06:29,519
Elevator to five.

59
00:06:31,941 --> 00:06:35,277
Had to go in to change
the locks, you know?

60
00:06:35,278 --> 00:06:36,283
How come?

61
00:06:36,379 --> 00:06:38,080
Well, the police had to break
the door open...,

62
00:06:38,081 --> 00:06:40,215
...you know, when they found her.

63
00:06:40,216 --> 00:06:42,451
I didn't charge you for it,
though.

64
00:06:42,452 --> 00:06:44,283
Thanks.

65
00:06:58,134 --> 00:06:59,761
Going up?

66
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:51,784
Ow!

67
00:11:51,894 --> 00:11:52,918
Damn it.

68
00:12:21,691 --> 00:12:22,891
What do you mean,
what do I mean?

69
00:12:22,892 --> 00:12:23,992
Where were you?

70
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:26,561
I was just here
inside the house.

71
00:12:26,562 --> 00:12:28,163
You were just here inside
of the house.

72
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:29,698
Now, how come I saw you
out by that door?

73
00:12:29,699 --> 00:12:33,139
What are you doing at that door?

74
00:12:36,606 --> 00:12:37,706
You weren't there?

75
00:12:37,707 --> 00:12:40,699
What, am I seeing things?

76
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,163
I really don't understand.

77
00:13:01,164 --> 00:13:03,169
What happened here?

78
00:13:19,682 --> 00:13:22,350
Oh, there's another story again.

79
00:13:22,351 --> 00:13:23,552
No, it's not a story.

80
00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:25,612
She wanted to play.

81
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,155
She can play inside
the apartment.

82
00:13:27,156 --> 00:13:32,841
Why do you have to play with her
out in the hallway?

83
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:53,400
I'll be right with you.

84
00:14:53,509 --> 00:14:54,676
What do you guys want?

85
00:14:54,677 --> 00:14:55,777
Tell me what's good here.

86
00:14:55,778 --> 00:14:58,679
Listen.

87
00:14:58,781 --> 00:15:00,942
Hey.

88
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:07,046
Can you excuse me?

89
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:08,282
Hi.

90
00:15:11,594 --> 00:15:13,984
When did you get back?

91
00:15:14,764 --> 00:15:16,294
A couple days.

92
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,556
Are you here for good?

93
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:20,819
I hope so.

94
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,145
I'm sorry about your mom...
I...I heard what happened.

95
00:15:30,146 --> 00:15:34,105
Yeah, it's...

96
00:15:34,216 --> 00:15:35,317
You look great.

97
00:15:35,318 --> 00:15:37,149
No, no, I don't.

98
00:15:37,253 --> 00:15:40,055
You don't have to say that.

99
00:15:40,056 --> 00:15:42,190
Maybe a cup of coffee
or something later?

100
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:44,192
I can't.
I have finals.

101
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:46,194
School?
You're going to school?

102
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,628
Yep.

103
00:15:47,730 --> 00:15:49,355
That's amazing.

104
00:15:49,432 --> 00:15:51,566
I have to design
an entire line by next week.

105
00:15:51,567 --> 00:15:54,400
It's...

106
00:15:54,503 --> 00:15:56,338
...everything's really different
for me now.

107
00:15:56,339 --> 00:15:57,672
Yeah, maybe another time.

108
00:15:57,673 --> 00:15:59,874
Maybe this weekend, maybe...

109
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:02,143
I'm working doubles
and school...,

110
00:16:02,144 --> 00:16:06,059
...and, look,
I have zero free time.

111
00:16:06,649 --> 00:16:09,084
I don't think it's a good idea.

112
00:16:09,085 --> 00:16:12,095
Can we get the bill, please?

113
00:16:12,188 --> 00:16:13,288
I'm sorry.

114
00:16:13,289 --> 00:16:16,224
I have to get back to work.

115
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:17,325
It's good to see you.

116
00:16:17,326 --> 00:16:18,326
You too.

117
00:17:29,265 --> 00:17:31,460
Help me.

118
00:17:49,285 --> 00:17:52,652
See anything wrong?

119
00:17:52,755 --> 00:17:55,590
Got to be a loose
brake pad spring.

120
00:17:55,591 --> 00:17:56,691
You're sure about that?

121
00:17:56,692 --> 00:17:57,859
Guy complained of a rattle...

122
00:17:57,860 --> 00:17:59,461
...when he drives over bumps,
right?

123
00:17:59,462 --> 00:18:01,089
That's right.

124
00:18:01,197 --> 00:18:03,498
You know how to check for
misfires in alignment pressure?

125
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:07,435
Yeah.

126
00:18:09,472 --> 00:18:12,607
Look, I've got to be honest
with you.

127
00:18:12,608 --> 00:18:13,708
Involuntary manslaughter...,

128
00:18:13,709 --> 00:18:15,243
...that's not exactly
a minor offense, you know?

129
00:18:15,244 --> 00:18:17,745
If I had more to offer you
than my word...,

130
00:18:17,746 --> 00:18:18,847
...I would give it to you, man.

131
00:18:18,848 --> 00:18:24,198
But I'm just trying to put
my life back together.

132
00:18:25,988 --> 00:18:27,088
Pay ain't high.

133
00:18:27,089 --> 00:18:29,649
I don't need much.

134
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:34,295
If I hire you, I just ask you
to be straight with me.

135
00:18:34,296 --> 00:18:35,396
All right?

136
00:18:35,464 --> 00:18:37,031
It took me a long time
to build this shop...,

137
00:18:37,032 --> 00:18:38,500
...and I don't want anything
risking that.

138
00:18:38,501 --> 00:18:39,601
You understand?

139
00:18:39,602 --> 00:18:43,638
Give me one week,
and I'll show you what I can do.

140
00:18:43,639 --> 00:18:45,640
Come back tomorrow.

141
00:18:45,641 --> 00:18:46,741
Thank you.

142
00:18:46,742 --> 00:18:49,302
All right.

143
00:18:49,411 --> 00:18:50,751
Sir, get up.

144
00:19:03,959 --> 00:19:08,293
It's suppertime.

145
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:10,167
He won't answer.

146
00:19:12,935 --> 00:19:15,303
Got some plumbing problems,
I think.

147
00:19:15,304 --> 00:19:19,459
Like, I'm hearing noises
in the walls.

148
00:19:34,123 --> 00:19:36,178
Patrol and unit 25.

149
00:19:46,802 --> 00:19:48,237
We get calls.

150
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:52,934
This is a code four
on First and Broadway.

151
00:19:53,042 --> 00:19:54,047
Code two.

152
00:19:54,143 --> 00:19:56,737
Get 6544.

153
00:20:34,016 --> 00:20:36,348
Great.

154
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:43,358
Miss Trupiano?

155
00:20:43,459 --> 00:20:45,825
Bobby Reynolds.

156
00:20:45,928 --> 00:20:46,928
Yeah.

157
00:20:47,029 --> 00:20:48,730
Yeah, from high school.

158
00:20:48,731 --> 00:20:53,668
Uh, yeah, I was released.

159
00:20:53,769 --> 00:20:56,499
Is Louis there?

160
00:20:56,605 --> 00:20:58,505
Oh, yeah?

161
00:20:58,607 --> 00:21:02,477
You got a forwarding number
maybe or...

162
00:21:02,478 --> 00:21:05,038
Hello?

163
00:21:05,147 --> 00:21:08,139
Hello?

164
00:21:11,754 --> 00:21:13,655
She's got the dirty mouth
from the South.

165
00:21:13,656 --> 00:21:15,657
All the way from Pascagoula,
Mississippi...,

166
00:21:15,658 --> 00:21:17,903
...it's Molly Ritter.

167
00:23:32,594 --> 00:23:35,363
You handle all the apartments
in the building, man?

168
00:23:35,364 --> 00:23:36,731
Who's been in mine?

169
00:23:36,732 --> 00:23:38,566
You have the only key.

170
00:23:38,567 --> 00:23:40,398
Everything okay?

171
00:23:43,138 --> 00:23:44,867
I found these.

172
00:23:48,577 --> 00:23:49,677
They're fingernails.

173
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:50,912
I know what they are, man.

174
00:23:50,913 --> 00:23:52,280
Why...why are they in my place?

175
00:23:52,281 --> 00:23:53,381
Who would keep 'em?

176
00:23:53,382 --> 00:23:55,650
Maybe they belong
to your mother?

177
00:23:55,651 --> 00:23:58,136
Why would she keep 'em?

178
00:23:58,821 --> 00:24:02,261
When did you
speak to her last?

179
00:24:02,324 --> 00:24:03,424
Couple of years.

180
00:24:03,425 --> 00:24:06,093
Yeah, you shouldn't have
to hear this from me...,

181
00:24:06,094 --> 00:24:08,896
...but the neighbors heard
from the police.

182
00:24:08,897 --> 00:24:11,933
Your mother locked herself
in her apartment for weeks...

183
00:24:11,934 --> 00:24:15,392
...before she died.

184
00:24:15,504 --> 00:24:18,871
What?

185
00:24:18,974 --> 00:24:20,608
You got any idea
why she would do that?

186
00:24:20,609 --> 00:24:22,372
No idea.

187
00:24:22,478 --> 00:24:23,911
I started work here after.

188
00:24:23,912 --> 00:24:25,480
I never met her.

189
00:24:25,481 --> 00:24:28,082
But when they found her,
she was in real bad shape.

190
00:24:28,083 --> 00:24:31,314
You never knew about this?

191
00:24:31,420 --> 00:24:33,588
Nobody check in on her?

192
00:24:33,589 --> 00:24:37,389
She didn't have
anybody else, man.

193
00:24:37,493 --> 00:24:39,260
Maybe one of the neighbors
upstairs knows more.

194
00:24:39,261 --> 00:24:40,361
Well, no offense, son...,

195
00:24:40,362 --> 00:24:42,363
...but nobody here wants
to talk to you.

196
00:24:42,364 --> 00:24:44,765
Everybody knows you were
in prison.

197
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:46,666
People talk.

198
00:24:46,768 --> 00:24:48,970
She was sick, real sick.

199
00:24:48,971 --> 00:24:49,971
Yeah.

200
00:24:50,072 --> 00:24:51,906
You...you gonna check
on those noises?

201
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:53,040
What noises?

202
00:24:53,041 --> 00:24:54,441
In the walls.

203
00:24:54,476 --> 00:24:55,643
Rusty pipes, I don't know.

204
00:24:55,644 --> 00:24:57,845
They're coming
from somewhere, man.

205
00:24:57,846 --> 00:24:59,814
Well, this is a prewar building.

206
00:24:59,815 --> 00:25:01,082
You know, walls are thick.

207
00:25:01,083 --> 00:25:02,884
There's vents running through
the ceiling.

208
00:25:02,885 --> 00:25:04,619
There's no sound.

209
00:25:04,620 --> 00:25:09,300
You seem to be the only one
hearing things.

210
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,601
- I wasn't there.
- You weren't there?

211
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:23,938
What am I...
am I seeing things?

212
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:25,640
I...I don't know what you're
talking about.

213
00:25:25,641 --> 00:25:27,642
Why do you keep lying to me
all the time?

214
00:25:27,643 --> 00:25:28,743
I'm not lying to you.

215
00:25:28,744 --> 00:25:29,911
What, I go to work all day.

216
00:25:29,912 --> 00:25:31,212
I come home and what?

217
00:25:31,213 --> 00:25:32,380
No, just just stop.

218
00:25:32,381 --> 00:25:33,481
Who is this guy?

219
00:25:33,482 --> 00:25:34,482
Stop.

220
00:25:34,583 --> 00:25:35,607
Stop it.

221
00:25:35,717 --> 00:25:37,116
Please.

222
00:25:37,219 --> 00:25:39,186
Well, you're acting like I'm...
what, like...what am I?

223
00:25:39,187 --> 00:25:40,288
Am I the bad guy here?

224
00:25:40,289 --> 00:25:41,455
You're the one that's out...

225
00:25:41,456 --> 00:25:42,690
No, no, no, no,
I didn't say that.

226
00:25:42,691 --> 00:25:43,791
I didn't say it.

227
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:45,459
Well, what the hell
were you doing there?

228
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:47,328
I wasn't doing anything.

229
00:25:47,329 --> 00:25:49,096
I don't want to catch you
by that door again.

230
00:25:49,097 --> 00:25:52,089
Are you all right in there?

231
00:26:11,853 --> 00:26:13,688
All right, we'll start you off
with tune-ups.

232
00:26:13,689 --> 00:26:15,122
We'll see how fast you work.

233
00:26:15,123 --> 00:26:17,124
You're also going to bring
the cars in and park them...

234
00:26:17,125 --> 00:26:18,426
...behind the gate every night.

235
00:26:18,427 --> 00:26:20,127
It's freshman work,
but you're the new guy.

236
00:26:20,128 --> 00:26:21,295
You show me you got skills,

237
00:26:21,296 --> 00:26:22,964
I'll give you more shifts
and bigger jobs.

238
00:26:22,965 --> 00:26:24,495
You hear that?

239
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:27,195
What?

240
00:26:27,302 --> 00:26:28,737
Like a voice.

241
00:26:28,804 --> 00:26:30,571
It's a valve grinder.

242
00:26:30,572 --> 00:26:34,133
Car keys are in there.

243
00:26:38,714 --> 00:26:40,149
What is that?

244
00:26:40,182 --> 00:26:41,649
That's the drop-box.

245
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:45,453
Don't give keys out till
the customer's paid in full.

246
00:26:45,454 --> 00:26:46,554
You got it?

247
00:26:46,555 --> 00:26:49,390
Had a lot of cars jacked
from this shop.

248
00:26:49,391 --> 00:26:52,593
Can't risk that kind
of nonsense anymore.

249
00:26:52,594 --> 00:26:54,425
Yo!

250
00:26:54,529 --> 00:26:57,293
You with me?

251
00:26:57,399 --> 00:27:01,426
Yeah.

252
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:03,060
Yeah.

253
00:27:03,171 --> 00:27:04,171
Good.

254
00:27:04,272 --> 00:27:06,035
Get to work.

255
00:27:19,488 --> 00:27:21,979
Two sugars, no milk.

256
00:27:22,090 --> 00:27:24,910
I switched to Sweet'N Low.

257
00:27:24,993 --> 00:27:30,090
Are you gonna knock it,
or you gonna drink it?

258
00:27:35,937 --> 00:27:37,772
You call anyone
from the neighborhood yet?

259
00:27:37,773 --> 00:27:39,340
Yeah, I called around.

260
00:27:39,341 --> 00:27:41,542
Seems like everybody moved away.

261
00:27:41,543 --> 00:27:42,942
Hmm.

262
00:27:43,045 --> 00:27:44,578
People grew up.

263
00:27:44,579 --> 00:27:48,616
Things ain't what
they used to be, right?

264
00:27:48,617 --> 00:27:50,384
Did you think everything
would be the same?

265
00:27:50,385 --> 00:27:54,110
I was hoping
some things would be.

266
00:27:55,891 --> 00:27:56,891
Bobby...

267
00:27:56,992 --> 00:27:58,292
I know you got questions.

268
00:27:58,293 --> 00:27:59,493
No, no,
I don't have questions.

269
00:27:59,494 --> 00:28:00,594
I had questions...,

270
00:28:00,595 --> 00:28:02,997
...had questions for the past
few years.

271
00:28:02,998 --> 00:28:07,968
I stopped asking them
when you stopped writing.

272
00:28:07,969 --> 00:28:13,129
I didn't know if you were alive
or coming back.

273
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:18,045
Why on Earth
would you just cut me off?

274
00:28:18,046 --> 00:28:20,214
I thought I was
doing it for you.

275
00:28:20,215 --> 00:28:21,546
